An IPv6 address is a 128-bit number as described [here][1]. A long in Java is represented on 64 bits, so you need another structure, like a BigDecimal or two longs (a container with an array of two longs or simply an array of two longs) in order to store an IPv6 address.


  [1]: https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc4291

Below is an example (just to provide you an idea):


